Hi Stefan.  Thanks for listening.  I figured at this point, the closest to a two-way 
conversation I could get would be to shorten the time between listening to what has been 
said.  

The purple deer comment made me laugh too (by they way, Arthur told me purple deer eat 
apples - LOL), and the way he repeated, &quot;I told you purple deer&quot; made me laugh too ... I 
wondered if perhaps he&#39;d gotten a little frustrated with me.

Yes, that is the correct name of Tom&#39;s cat (though not well enunciated) and I&#39;ve forwarded 
the clip to him, but I know he gets a ton a email so it may take a short while to hear back.

I&#39;m wondering the same thing about the techs.  It would certainly make sense for them to 
have specialty areas, but still know each other (much like it works in our world).  Patrick 
and David also use the MiniBox.  What I&#39;m wondering, and will try next, is to see of Arthur 
can use the manual sweep.  

I&#39;ll keep you posted.  :-)

Margaret 

