&gt; 
&gt; &gt; I ran a bunch of short sessions tonight (about 20 seconds each) asking a question, 
&gt; &gt; listening for the answer, then going onto the next based on what I heard previously. 
Most 
&gt; &gt; of these answers came very quickly. I have removed all of the non-relevant sound 
between 
&gt; &gt; Q&A, but very little has been modified in the answering phrase itself (just made them 
so it 
&gt; &gt; didn&#39;t sound like a stutter.)  Parts 4, 5, 6, and 7 were from a single session, because I 
was 
&gt; &gt; hearing the answer real-time, but not understanding it.  I thought Arthur was trying 
to tell 
&gt; &gt; me specifically what kid of pet.  Likewise, the last 2 parts were together in one 
session.
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; I have lowered my voice to hopefully make the responses more clear. I&#39;m working to 
&gt; &gt; establish whether or not there is any indication of probable intentional 
communication 
&gt; &gt; taking place. So far, I&#39;d say there are very strong indicators.  
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; Can you say A.B.C.?
&gt; &gt; &quot;A.B.C.D.E.&quot;  (this answer is sort of buried in the main sound)
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; How about Tom Butler?
&gt; &gt; &quot;Tom Butler.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; Do you know the name of either of Tom Butler&#39;s cats?
&gt; &gt; &quot;(Sh)asta&#39;s their cat.&quot; (the &quot;Sh&quot; sound is weak or missing)
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; Do you have any pets?
&gt; &gt; &quot;I have a pet.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; I heard you say I have a...?
&gt; &gt; &quot;Pet.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; You have a what?
&gt; &gt; &quot;Pet.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; What kind of pet do you have?
&gt; &gt; &quot;An animal.&quot; (LOL- ask a silly question, get a silly answer!)
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; I understand you have a pet animal, but what is the species?
&gt; &gt; &quot;A purple deer.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; OK, I could have sworn you said you have a purple deer.
&gt; &gt; &quot;I told you purple deer.&quot; 
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; OK, I&#39;m gonna close for the evening.  Can you tell me goodbye?
&gt; &gt; &quot;I love you.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; I heard you say I love you.  Love you too.
&gt; &gt; &quot;Thank you.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; The speed for this session was set on 106%, which is a little too fast for listening on 
&gt; &gt; playback, but I get good responses with the setting.  I have slowed the tempo on the 
&gt; &gt; answers by -18 in order to make them just a little clearer.  :-)
